<br>
I wouldn't be concerned that someone's vector-of-choice for friendships involves a medium such as the game.  In many cases it can be better than the people you would normally have to choose from for social contacts.<br>
<br>
What I find tragic is that someone -knew- the guy had problems and didn't get him the help he needed.  Or that the guy didn't want it.   <p><table border=1 bgcolor="#161C81"width=80%>
